The screen object is called a surface. Each element in the game like alien or ship, is a surface. 
Each element on the screen is its own surface. The display.flip() rewrites onto the screen every iteration of loop.
The background color only has to be specified once. Pygame uses a RGB color system, each color ranging from 0-255. (255, 0, 0) = red. etc.
Each number is telling the computer to mix certain amounts of these colors

Create a separate module for settings of game, to have everything in one place for changing settings. Make it a class.


